2. cs.LG - The paper involves analyzing and evaluating various configurations of compiled knowledge, which can be seen as a machine learning problem. 
3. cs.DS - The paper discusses procedures for selecting a subset of observations to incorporate into a compiled mapping, which can be seen as a data selection problem. 
4. cs.SE - The paper discusses engineering settings and methods for selecting the best pieces of evidence to incorporate into a compiled mapping, which can be seen as a software engineering problem. 
5. cs.PL - The paper discusses the costs of run-time delays and memory, which can be seen as a programming languages problem related to optimization and efficiency.
